The root always gets `aria-orientation`, but `root_role()` returns `role="group"` for `Multiple` and `None` modes; `aria-orientation` is not supported on `group`, so those modes emit invalid ARIA and are likely to fail accessibility linting. Only emit `aria-orientation` when the root role supports it (e.g., `radiogroup`) or switch to a role that legally carries orientation metadata.

